Package org.apache.sis.openoffice

Apache SIS services made available to Apache OpenOffice or LibreOffice. Functions to make available in OpenOffice are defined in X*.idl files, which are converted to X*.java files for convenience.

Note that the X*.class files to be included in the final JAR file shall be compiled from the X*.idl files, not from the X*.java files. See application/sis-openoffice/src/main/unopkg/build-instruction.html for more information.

Since:
0.8

Defined in the sis-openoffice module

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    XReferencing
    Services from the org.apache.sis.referencing package to be exported to Apache OpenOffice or LibreOffice.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CalcAddins
    Base class for methods to export as formulas in the Apache OpenOffice spread sheet.
    ReferencingFunctions
    Implements the XReferencing methods to make available to Apache OpenOffice.
    Registration
    The registration of all formulas provided in this package.
